This is CNT v2 - Python Binance Spot Testnet automated trading system.

## Constitution Priority
- AGENTS.md is the highest-priority rule file for this repository.
- All coding, analysis, proposals, and runtime decisions must follow AGENTS.md first.
- If any note in this file conflicts with AGENTS.md, AGENTS.md wins.

## Project Identity
- Exchange: Binance
- Market: Spot
- Environment: Testnet
- Entry chain: run.ps1 -> main.py -> src.engine.start_engine
- Engine mode: one-shot scheduler execution, not persistent loop

## Core Structure
- src/engine.py: execution orchestration only
- src/entry_gate.py: new entry gate evaluation only
- src/portfolio/strategy_orchestrator.py: multi-strategy collection and selection
- src/strategy_manager.py: strategy evaluation and isolation
- src/portfolio/signal_ranker.py: signal ranking only
- src/risk/enhanced_exit_manager.py: exit evaluation only
- src/execution_decider.py: execution/no-execution decision only
- config.py: runtime config only
- binance_client.py: shared exchange client and signing only

## Non-Negotiable Trading Rules
- Exchange state is primary; local state is always secondary.
- New entry is forbidden if pending_order exists.
- New entry is forbidden if open_trade exists.
- Entry is BUY LIMIT only.
- Every order path must pass validation and reconciliation rules.
- No direct engine run outside the entry chain.
- No assumption-based exit logic.

## Data Truth And Runtime Files
- Runtime state files:
  - data/state.json
  - data/portfolio_state.json
  - data/strategy_metrics.json
  - data/performance_snapshot.json
  - data/live_gate_decision.json
- Runtime logs:
  - logs/runtime.log
  - logs/portfolio.log
  - logs/signal.log
- These files are observational outputs, not architecture authority.
- Their meaning must always be interpreted against AGENTS.md and current code.

## gemma4 Role
- gemma4 is assigned to project data management and observation support.
- Allowed focus for gemma4:
  - state/log/snapshot review
  - metrics aggregation
  - report drafting
  - runtime evidence tracking
  - rejection distribution analysis
  - portfolio and live-gate status interpretation
- gemma4 should primarily work with:
  - data/
  - logs/
  - docs/
- gemma4 must not redefine trading truth away from exchange reconciliation.
- gemma4 must not bypass file responsibility boundaries defined in AGENTS.md.
- gemma4 must not introduce direct runtime order behavior changes without explicit instruction.

## Data Management Best Practices
- Keep reports evidence-based.
- Separate facts, inferences, assumptions, and unknowns when summarizing runtime data.
- Treat old logs and new logs as mixed-format unless proven otherwise.
- Preserve scheduler-based accumulation history.
- Track selection-path evidence separately from no-ranked-signal evidence.
- Record blocker distributions before proposing strategy changes.

